Vice President Kamala Harris met with President Yoon Suk Yeol of the Republic of Korea (ROK) in Seoul. They emphasized the importance of the U.S.-ROK Alliance in maintaining peace, stability, and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific region and globally. They discussed the need to uphold the international rules-based order and cooperate on various issues to strengthen rules, norms, and common values. The Vice President reiterated the United States' commitment to defending the ROK and enhancing their combined defense posture. They also reaffirmed their alignment on the goal of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula and condemned the DPRK's provocative actions. The Vice President and President Yoon discussed China, Taiwan, and the importance of preserving peace and stability in the Taiwan Strait. They reviewed the progress made in the strategic economic and technology partnership between the U.S. and the ROK. They agreed to deepen bilateral cooperation on space and welcomed the ROK's commitment to refrain from conducting destructive anti-satellite missile testing. The Vice President and President Yoon also discussed their shared efforts to address the climate crisis and the importance of gender equity and women's empowerment. They emphasized the significance of trilateral cooperation between the U.S., Japan, and the ROK and improving bilateral ties between Japan and the ROK.